From ea33584435032782be6322c25ffc0ee41ae3ceec Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 2026 14:32:38 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 3/5] feat: resource-diet profile: ONNX backend, preload
 gunicorn, scoped sessions, L2 cache

Fase 2 of the plain-text manager plan:
- OnnxEmbeddingAdapter (onnxruntime + tokenizers, optional extra
  'onnx'): small multilingual model in int8 replaces the ~2.2 GB torch
  e5-large footprint per process; selected via EMBEDDING_BACKEND=onnx
- gunicorn.conf.py with preload_app so the model and mmap'd index load
  once in the master and are shared by forked workers; Dockerfile now
  uses the config file
- SQLAlchemy sessions request-scoped (scoped_session + teardown), fixing
  the wsgi.py known single-session simplification
- L2 search-result cache behind a SearchResultCache port: in-memory
  LRU+TTL fallback, RedisSearchCache (generation-counter invalidation,
  cross-worker) when REDIS_URL set; /search reads it, /index and DELETE
  invalidate the tenant namespace
- optional extras onnx/redis in pyproject; .env.example documents the
  low-RAM profile; 205 tests green

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
